        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2021-08-25 14:40:22.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nRenaming a bunch of files just to re-order (or insert/remove) items seems a bit tedious.  Maybe in Jakarta, we can re-think this strategy.  Perhaps we eliminate the prefixes and then add a single file, for each schema version, which lists the order of each script to be executed.  That same file would be used for both upgrades and downgrades.  I know we discussed this briefly during the design phase, but now the actual implementation is exposing the deficiencies in the current approach.",
        "patchset_number": 1
      },
      {
