          "email": "ramkrishna.verma@gmail.com",
          "username": "ramverma"
        },
        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2021-08-25 14:43:13.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1: Code-Review+1\n\n> Patch Set 1:\n> \n> Renaming a bunch of files just to re-order (or insert/remove) items seems a bit tedious.  Maybe in Jakarta, we can re-think this strategy.  Perhaps we eliminate the prefixes and then add a single file, for each schema version, which lists the order of each script to be executed.  That same file would be used for both upgrades and downgrades.  I know we discussed this briefly during the design phase, but now the actual implementation is exposing the deficiencies in the current approach.\n\nAgree, in that case sequencing can be made through a single file.",
        "patchset_number": 1
      },
      {
